BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dst-start-2026@civic
SUMMARY:Daylight Saving Time Begins
DESCRIPTION:Clocks spring forward one hour at 2:00 AM on the second Sunday of March. Daylight saving time extends evening daylight through the warmer months. Remember: Spring forward\, fall back.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260308
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260309
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:taxday-2026@civic
SUMMARY:Tax Day
DESCRIPTION:The deadline for filing U.S. federal individual income tax returns with the IRS. If April 15 falls on a weekend or holiday\, the deadline is moved to the next business day.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260415
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260416
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dst-end-2026@civic
SUMMARY:Daylight Saving Time Ends
DESCRIPTION:Clocks fall back one hour at 2:00 AM on the first Sunday of November. Standard time resumes until the following spring. Remember: Spring forward\, fall back.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261102
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:electionday-2026@civic
SUMMARY:Election Day
DESCRIPTION:The Tuesday after the first Monday in November is the date for federal\, state\, and local elections. Presidential elections occur every four years (2028\, 2032\, 2036). Midterm elections occur in even non-presidential years.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261103
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261104
END:VEVENT

